      return `
        &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;${product.productInfo.title}&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;${product.productInfo.description}&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;${product.productInfo.price}&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;${product.qty}&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;button class=&#39;remove&#39;&gt;Remove Item&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;/tr&gt;`;
    }

You can style the table using it&#39;s id &quot;productTable&quot; via css.
The last entry of every row also contains a dynamically created button of class &quot;remove&quot; for which you can write your javascript code to remove items. Again just an example, you can create arbitrary html markup dynamically with this method .

