    void** argtab= malloc(sizeof(struct argnum)*(argc-1));

Why do you declare `argtab` as a `void **`? If you need an array of structures, you have to declare it this way:

    struct argnum *argtab = malloc(sizeof(struct argnum) * (argc-1));

Now the compiler is aware that `argtab` is not just a &quot;bag of bytes&quot; but a structure whose fields it knows.

Also it is unusual, though allowed, to declare a structure inside a function.

